csExportItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_4091963\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_4091963\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 12, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104bgv1665702551096_2.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/bgv1665702551096_2.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/bgv1665702551096_2.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"bgv1665702551096\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">Global Objects\n      \n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"bgv1665702551096__global_objects_88044\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">A global object is a reusable, technology-independent object that is centrally stored and available to all components running on a given host, regardless of the deployment environment.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"bgv1665702551096__p_d26390e1_d26391e1_d26392e1\">Global objects are stored in runtime libraries. They are not statically bound to components and application shells . Instead, when executing a component that references a global object, Uniface locates the object in the appropriate library and resolves the reference at runtime. This makes it possible to modify global objects without recompiling the components and application shells that use them.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"bgv1665702551096__p_d26393e1_d26394e1_d26395e1\">Global objects can use other global objects. For example,\n         a component can call a global ProcScript function that uses global messages.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"bgv1665702551096__p_d26396e1_d26397e1_d26398e1\">For text-based global objects, such as messages and menus, the containing library is language-specific. Uniface determines which message to display at runtime based the on information it has about the current environment. Both the library and the language can be set when the application is started.</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"bgv1665702551096__table_d2783e1_d2784e1_d2785e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Types of Global Objects</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"bgv1665702551096__table_d2783e1_d2784e1_d2785e1__entry__1\">\n Global Object\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"bgv1665702551096__table_d2783e1_d2784e1_d2785e1__entry__2\">\n Purpose\n </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bgv1665702551096__table_d2783e1_d2784e1_d2785e1__entry__1\">\n Global constants\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bgv1665702551096__table_d2783e1_d2784e1_d2785e1__entry__2\">Named constant values that can be accessed by all\n                     ProcScript in the application. <div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"bgv1665702551096__note_w2793ab1b5c11b3b7b1b3b1_w2794ab1b5c11b3b7b1b3_w2795ab1b5c11b3b7b1_w2796ab1b5c11b3b7_w2797ab1b5c11b3_w2798ab1b5c11_w2799ab1b5_w2800ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> Unlike other global objects, global constants are defined in an\n                        IncludeScript with the fixed name <code class=\"ph codeph\">DEFPARAM</code>. For more\n                        information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"mid1707825339751.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/mid1707825339751.html\" title=\"Global constants must be defined in an IncludeScript called DEFPARAM.\">Define a Global Constant</a>. </div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bgv1665702551096__table_d2783e1_d2784e1_d2785e1__entry__1\">\n Global variables\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bgv1665702551096__table_d2783e1_d2784e1_d2785e1__entry__2\">\n Typed variables that can be accessed by all ProcScript in the application. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"clk1665702551274.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/clk1665702551274.html\" title=\"Variables are placeholders for data whose value can change during the runtime duration of the ProcScript module, component, or application for which they have scope. The scope is determined by where they are declared.\">Variables</a>.\n               </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bgv1665702551096__table_d2783e1_d2784e1_d2785e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"cvq1665702579531.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/cvq1665702579531.html\" title=\"Global ProcScripts are global objects that are located in a runtime library and can be called from any ProcScript in the application. They enable you to define common functionality for use by one or more applications.\">Global ProcScripts</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bgv1665702551096__table_d2783e1_d2784e1_d2785e1__entry__2\">\n ProcScript modules that can be called by any ProcScript in the application.\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bgv1665702551096__table_d2783e1_d2784e1_d2785e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"hir1705568318852.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/hir1705568318852.html\" title=\"Messages are language-related objects that enable you to deploy a Uniface application in different languages and locales. They are stored in language-specific libraries, and Uniface automatically chooses the appropriate library at runtime based on the configuration.\">Messages</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bgv1665702551096__table_d2783e1_d2784e1_d2785e1__entry__2\">\n Language-specific objects that can be used in labels, help text, prompts, error messages, and so on. They include messages, help texts, and language setups.\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bgv1665702551096__table_d2783e1_d2784e1_d2785e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"vfw1705577424699.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/vfw1705577424699.html\" title=\"Uniface enables you to define menu bar, drop-down menu, and pop-up menu objects for use in Windows applications.\">Menu Objects</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bgv1665702551096__table_d2783e1_d2784e1_d2785e1__entry__2\">\n Language-specific definitions of menu bars, menus , and pop-up menus for desktop applications.\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bgv1665702551096__table_d2783e1_d2784e1_d2785e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"byf1705583062647.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/byf1705583062647.html\" title=\"Panels are global objects that are typically used to create toolbars for form components and application shells. They contain buttons to execute structure editor functions and activate component operations.\">Panels</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bgv1665702551096__table_d2783e1_d2784e1_d2785e1__entry__2\">\n Toolbars containing buttons to execute structure editor functions and operations on the active form (desktop applications only).\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bgv1665702551096__table_d2783e1_d2784e1_d2785e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"xzb1705583342348.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/xzb1705583342348.html\" title=\"Drag-and-drop formats are global objects that define drag and drop behavior, including the default action, pop-up menu, and icon that are available when performing drag and drop actions in the tree and picture widgets. They are not used for drag-and-drop widgets.\">Drag-and-Drop Formats</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bgv1665702551096__table_d2783e1_d2784e1_d2785e1__entry__2\">\n Language-specific definitions for the pop-up menu, icon, and default action for drag-and-drop actions in specific widgets.\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bgv1665702551096__table_d2783e1_d2784e1_d2785e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"nbf1705582294349.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/nbf1705582294349.html\" title=\"Glyphs are images in a Uniface-proprietary format, which can be used as background images in forms, entities and application shells, and as icons in widgets, panel buttons, menus, and drag-and-drop formats.\">Glyphs</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bgv1665702551096__table_d2783e1_d2784e1_d2785e1__entry__2\">\n Images in a Uniface-proprietary format, which can be used as background images in forms, entities and application shells, and as icons in widgets, panel buttons, menus, and drag-and-drop formats.\n </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_4091963\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_4091963\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Global Objects Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 12, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Global Objects A global object is a reusable, technology-independent object that is centrally stored and available to all components running on a given host, regardless of the deployment environment. Global objects are stored in runtime libraries. They are not statically bound to components and application shells . Instead, when executing a component that references a global object, Uniface locates the object in the appropriate library and resolves the reference at runtime. This makes it possible to modify global objects without recompiling the components and application shells that use them. Global objects can use other global objects. For example, a component can call a global ProcScript function that uses global messages. For text-based global objects, such as messages and menus, the containing library is language-specific. Uniface determines which message to display at runtime based the on information it has about the current environment. Both the library and the language can be set when the application is started. Table 1. Types of Global Objects Global Object Purpose Global constants Named constant values that can be accessed by all ProcScript in the application. Note: Unlike other global objects, global constants are defined in an IncludeScript with the fixed name DEFPARAM . For more information, see Define a Global Constant . Global variables Typed variables that can be accessed by all ProcScript in the application. For more information, see Variables . Global ProcScripts ProcScript modules that can be called by any ProcScript in the application. Messages Language-specific objects that can be used in labels, help text, prompts, error messages, and so on. They include messages, help texts, and language setups. Menu Objects Language-specific definitions of menu bars, menus , and pop-up menus for desktop applications. Panels Toolbars containing buttons to execute structure editor functions and operations on the active form (desktop applications only). Drag-and-Drop Formats Language-specific definitions for the pop-up menu, icon, and default action for drag-and-drop actions in specific widgets. Glyphs Images in a Uniface-proprietary format, which can be used as background images in forms, entities and application shells, and as icons in widgets, panel buttons, menus, and drag-and-drop formats. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}